Comment:
A Cozy Haven for Coffee Aficionados:

Nestled in the heart of the city, Third Wave Coffee House is a hidden gem that beckons coffee lovers with its aromatic brews and warm ambiance. From the moment you step inside, you’re enveloped in the comforting aroma of freshly ground beans—a promise of good things to come day and night as it's open 24/7.

Service: The hallmark of any great coffee spot is its service, and Third Wave Coffee House doesn’t disappoint. The staff here seem to have an innate ability to make you feel right at home. Whether you’re a regular or a first-timer, they greet you with genuine smiles and a willingness to cater to your coffee preferences.

Aarti’s Expertise: Ah, Aarti! She’s the embodiment of passion for coffee. On my recent visit, I had the pleasure of chatting with her about brewing methods. When I expressed curiosity about French press coffee, she practically lit up. Aarti patiently explained the process—the coarsely ground beans, the precise water temperature, and the gentle plunge. Her enthusiasm was contagious, and I left feeling like a budding barista myself.
Aarti guided me through the steps, and it was like a mini coffee ceremony. The rich aroma filled the air as she poured the hot water over the grounds, and we waited—patiently, as one does for good things. The result? A velvety, Dark Roast Vienna coffee cup that danced on my taste buds.

Ambiance: Third Wave Coffee House strikes the perfect balance between cozy and contemporary. Whether you’re catching up with friends, working on your laptop, reading a book with head phones on, or simply people-watching, this place feels like a warm hug.

Parting Thoughts: If you’re tired of generic coffee chains and crave something more personal, Third Wave Coffee House is where you belong.
Third Wave Coffee House is a haven for coffee aficionados, and Aarti’s passion adds that extra sprinkle of magic. So grab a seat, sip your brew, and let the world slow down for a while. ☕✨.

1. Fluctuating taste everytime (classic cold coffee). They have zero control on putting sugar, no matter how many times I tell them to put less sugar, they are unable to follow. Recently, they have started adding thick cream to the recipe too which is a big no!

2. Big problem is with thier ambiance! I have many times encountered a fly is sitting on the edge of my drinking cup or getting inside the straw. Such things actually ruin my mind.

Comment:
I visited Third Wave Coffee in Belapur CBD around 9 AM and was pleasantly surprised to find the place quite peaceful, with only two staff members present. I ordered an Americano, a Mexican Paneer Sandwich, and a Cappuccino. The sandwich was delicious, and both coffees were equally satisfying. The seating was comfortable, making it a great spot to relax or work.

However, parking could be a challenge if you’re in a four-wheeler, though it’s manageable for two-wheelers. Overall, it’s a nice spot to visit if you’re in the area, especially if you’re looking for good food and coffee in a comfortable setting.

We went into for a casual evening coffee which turned out to be a coffee learning day. I ordered a hot French vanilla latte and to my pleasant surprise I was approached by Nitin to teach me some coffee brewing techniques.

I really enjoyed this trip to TWC Indiranagar .
Good job Nitin and good luck to you in spreading the knowledge of coffee brewing!

Comment:
Third Wave Cafe - Pleasant Ambiance, Limited Food Options
Third Wave Cafe offers a pleasant ambiance, making it a relaxing spot to hang out or meet friends. The atmosphere is conducive to conversation and relaxation.

However, I was disappointed with the food options. The menu felt quite limited, and to my surprise, not all items were displayed. This led to an unfortunate order as I ended up with something I didn't enjoy after seeing a more appealing dish on someone else's table. Having the full menu visible would have prevented this.

While I appreciate the coffee options, my pistachio coffee was unfortunately unpleasant. It was so bad that I had to discard it. It would have been helpful if staff had checked on how we were enjoying our drinks.

I would recommend expanding the food menu and ensuring all available items are displayed clearly.

Comment:
Edited Review :- Excellent Cafe. There is a music band whose name is an anagram that only the band members know about. The name of this cafe sounded really cheesy when I heard it but I'm not sure if this is named after the "third wave coffee" business business and intended to be pun on the pandemic, much needed comic relief for everyone :D

That said each and every detail in this cafe seems to be handpicked, right from the interiors to the gourmet menu. The Pita bread and hummus I had was soul filling in every aspect, the taste, presentation, quality and quantity were all top notch, it made for a really sumptuous meal. Every branch of theirs has a signature vibe and little different from the other. The brownie I had there was also intense in flavor and was the right gooey, everything about the food here screams gourmet for sure. The himalayan green tea is accompanied by a neat sachet of a premium honey instead of sugar.

The place sure is a breakout from the hustle and bustle of the city and makes for a calm and serene place for some contemplative thinking or being productive. When I had to find a place to work "away from home" this place offered everything, a stable enterprise grade WiFi 6 connectivity that is easy to connect to. Just make sure to have a good mic on the headphone as it can be a little noisy at busy times, I had the Jabra Evolve 65 and the other person could not hear the subtle background noise and good music they were playing. More electric plug points and if I may crib, I could also ask for some USB power outlets on the table.

Worth a visit for sure if you have a chance.

The name of this cafe sounded really cheesy when I heard it but I'm not sure if this is named after the "third wave coffee" business business and intended to be pun on the pandemic, much needed comic relief for everyone :D

That said each and every detail in this cafe seems to be handpicked, right from the interiors to the gourmet menu. The Pita bread and hummus I had was soul filling in every aspect, the taste, presentation, quality and quantity were all top notch, it made for a really sumptuous meal. Every branch of theirs has a signature vibe and little different from the other. The brownie I had there was also intense in flavor and was the right gooey, everything about the food here screams gourmet for sure. The himalayan green tea is accompanied by a neat sachet of a premium honey instead of sugar.

The place sure is a breakout from the hustle and bustle of the city and makes for a calm and serene place for some contemplative thinking or being productive. **A Perfect Afternoon at Third Wave Coffee**

My recent visit to Third Wave Coffee was nothing short of extraordinary! The ambiance is cozy yet vibrant, making it the perfect spot to unwind or catch up with friends. But what truly made the experience memorable was the outstanding hospitality.

Rahul, Dhruv, Hassan, Mayank, and Aehbham went above and beyond to ensure that every guest felt welcome and taken care of. Their warmth and attentiveness made the afternoon special, and it was clear they genuinely love what they do.

The coffee, of course, was exceptional—crafted to perfection with rich, bold flavors that lingered long after the last sip. Pairing it with their delightful selection of treats made the experience even better.

If you're looking for a place that combines top-notch coffee with impeccable service, Third Wave Coffee is the place to be. I can't wait to return and enjoy another amazing afternoon with the best hosts in town!

Comment: This place makes my most favorite cold coffee that delivers to home here in Navi Mumbai. Thank you!

Third Wave Coffee in Bangalore is an absolute gem for coffee lovers and food enthusiasts alike. The coffee here is truly exceptional, crafted with great care and precision. Whether you're a fan of a classic espresso or enjoy exploring more unique brews, you won't be disappointed.

The Japanese cheesecake is a delightful treat—light, fluffy, and perfectly sweet. It's a must-try for anyone with a sweet tooth. The loaded crisps platter is another standout item, offering a delicious combination of flavors and textures that make for a satisfying snack or light meal.

What really sets Third Wave Coffee apart is their excellent customer service. The staff is incredibly attentive and takes the time to explain each product, helping you make the best choice based on your preferences. This level of engagement and knowledge sharing is truly impressive and adds a special touch to the experience.

The cafe also caters to working professionals, providing comfortable tables and a calm atmosphere that's conducive to getting work done. It's a perfect spot to grab a great cup of coffee, enjoy some delicious food, and get some work done in a relaxed environment.

Overall, Third Wave Coffee offers a fantastic combination of quality coffee, delectable treats, and top-notch service. It's a great place to visit, whether you're there to work or just to enjoy a leisurely coffee break. Highly recommended!

Comment:
I regularly visit Third Wave Coffee in Runwal Greens, and it has become my go-to spot for its fantastic ambiance and great crowd. The soothing music perfectly complements the vibrant atmosphere, making it an ideal place to relax or work. The service is outstanding, thanks to the incredibly courteous and friendly staff. Jessica and Neha, in particular, always greet you with a warm smile and are very cooperative. Neha’s attentiveness and Jessica’s knack for making every interaction special truly elevate the experience. Vignesh and Amit, the managers, ensure everything runs smoothly, while Chandan keeps the place impeccably clean.

My favorite drinks are the Chamomile Wellness, a calming choice perfect for unwinding, and the rich, robust Americano, ideal for a classic coffee taste. The food is equally impressive, with options like the unique charcoal chicken croissant and the deliciously satisfying chicken tandoori sandwich. What's great is that the food can be customized to suit your preferences, making it both stuffing, filling, and healthy. You won’t need to go anywhere else to satisfy your hunger pangs.

The cafe also offers great discounts if you use their app, adding to its appeal. Whether I’m here for a meeting, working from home, or just spending time alone or with friends, Third Wave Coffee provides a perfect setting. The free Wi-Fi makes it easy to get work done, and the view outside is especially lovely during the rains. It’s the perfect place to enjoy good coffee, delicious food, and exceptional service—all delivered with a smile.

Comment:
I went to this café with friends for a casual hangout on friendship day. Coffee was decent.
One of the staff members kept clearing our cups as soon as we were done, which gave me local Darshini hotel feels.
When we arrived, there were no available seats, so we adjusted at a table that was already occupied. After a while, the staff asked everyone at the table to move to different parts of the café, disrupting our conversation. They also kept asking how long we would stay, which felt like they were indirectly asking us to leave. We weren't using laptops or reading; we were just catching up with friends. I felt that this wasn't the right way to treat customers in a coffee place where people come to have a relaxed conversation over coffee. I'll probably avoid this place in the future.

Third wave coffee needs to make me their ambassador because I am the biggest fan of your dishes. I always fall in love with you'll again and again and again. Thank you for making me happy and making me a ambassador was sarcasm, please don't take it seriously

Comment:
I have been a patron of Third Wave Coffee for almost exactly one year now, out of which I have visited the Bellandur outlet the most, which makes me feel qualified to leave a detailed review of this cafe.

Service - The nicest folks who will treat you very well. I have been ordering an orange zest mocha with oatmilk from here so consistently that the cashier remembered my order today, which made feel a little special for sure, given the footfall this outlet experiences.

Food - The coffee is overall very good, but you come here for the speciality coffee drinks and ambience more than anything else. Blue Tokai may do coffee-coffee better, but their cafe experience is simply abysmal in comparison.
My favorites here are the orange zest mocha (clearly), the newly launched pistachio croissant, and the lemon raspberry tea cake.
They're always launching new items to keep things fresh, too.
Pricey for sure, goes without saying, but it is what you pay to use their reliable, free WiFi and stick around for the whole day if you so require.

The two cons as such that I would be remiss not to warn you about would be -
1) The bathroom is not as clean as you would hope.
2) On weekends, the outlet gets too crowded and loud, so it's better to visit on weekdays because you may not even get a seat on weekend evenings.

I’m an Ambassador level customer of Third Wave and visit their Sarjapur road outlet 2-3 times a week. And sometimes other outlets in the city when I am there.

Today I visited the TWC located inside Phoenix around 11:45am along-with a friend. Attended by a staff named Reeta or Rita. No greetings, no smile, not even a word spoken. On ordering, my friend was giving some requests, not even acknowledged with an ‘Ok’, it was like we were talking with a dead wall. Though a very sharp contrast to the other outlets where the staff is so good, but really doesn’t matter much to me.

On getting our hot cappuccino, on first 2 sips we felt that the milk was spoiled or something, we decided to leave the place and go to Starbucks, as we knew there is no point in speaking to this lady. We walked out, while my friends was still out, I took a u-turn and came to counter, and asked her, are you having abad day? No greeting, no acknowledgment of feedbacks, etc, all with smile and politely.

She blurted out to me “Full coffee khatam karne ka baad aaker idhar BAK diya kharaab hai, toh kya hum reolacement denge??”

So dear TWC, here is the thing:
1. No replacement was EVER sought by us, as were leaving for Starbucks, pls hear the conversation on your CCTV, I’m sure it’s voice enabled.

2. I took the cup from my table and put it on the counter in front of her, that cup is still full, she had no response to that. You may zoom your CCTV to see the cup. The other cup too was still more than 2/3 full, still on the table.

3. Finally, even if the replacement had been sought, is this the and attitude, tone and language your staff uses for you customer? “Bak diya”, really??

I’m quite well to do, don’t need free coffees, I give you enough business that you consider me at Ambassador level, but your staff is acting like they are doing charity to serve coffee which we have paid for?

The other staff Alwin (or a similar name) was just on his mobile sitting on a crate rather than greeting or serving customers. But the lady Rita/Reeta beats all records, the Gold Medal in customer dis-service definitely gies to her.

Had an exceptional experience. The ambiance was cozy and inviting, perfect for a relaxing break or catching up on work. The coffee was outstanding, with a rich and robust flavor that truly stands out.

What made my visit even more enjoyable was the excellent service provided by Shubham. He was incredibly friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. Shubham went out of his way to make sure I had everything I needed. It's employees like Shubham who elevate the overall experience and make customers feel valued.

Highly recommend Third Wave Coffee for anyone looking for great coffee and top-notch service!
